\Pi
y
\{0,1\}
L_{a,b}^0=\dfrac{b}{a+b}
L_{a,b}^1=\dfrac{a}{a+b}
 L_{a,b}^y=\int_0^1f_{Y\mid\Pi}(y\mid x)\cdot f_\Pi(x)\,\mathrm dx=\int_0^1x^y(1-x)^{1-y}\cdot\frac{\Gamma(a+b)}{\Gamma(a)\Gamma(b)}x^{a-1}(1-x)^{b-1}\,\mathrm dx, 
 L_{a,b}^y=\frac{\Gamma(a+b)}{\Gamma(a)\Gamma(b)}\cdot\frac{\Gamma(a+y)\Gamma(b+1-y)}{\Gamma(a+b+1)}. 
